---

# 4️⃣ SIGNATURE TYPES SUPPORTED

---

## 🔹 A. Simple Electronic Signature (SES)

* Checkbox confirmation
* OTP verification
* Email confirmation

Used for low-risk internal steps.

---

## 🔹 B. Advanced Electronic Signature (AES)

* Identity-linked
* Certificate-based
* Encrypted
* Unique to signatory

Used for:

* Bid submission
* Award confirmation

---

## 🔹 C. Qualified Digital Signature (QES-level equivalent)

* Government-approved certificate authority
* Strong cryptographic proof
* Highest evidentiary level

Used for:

* Contract signing
* High-value awards

System supports configurable levels based on risk/value.

---

# 5️⃣ DIGITAL SIGNATURE FLOW

---

## 🔹 A. Identity Validation (Precondition)

Before signing:

* Identity verified (Logic 1)
* Role authorized (Logic 2)
* Authority confirmed (Logic 11)

Only then can signature action proceed.

---

## 🔹 B. Document Hash Generation

Before signature:

```
Document → Cryptographic Hash Generated
```

Hash uniquely represents document contents.

If document changes → hash changes → signature invalid.

---

## 🔹 C. Signature Creation

```
User Private Key Encrypts Hash
↓
Signature Attached to Document
```

System stores:

* Encrypted signature
* Public certificate
* Timestamp
* IP/device metadata

---

## 🔹 D. Timestamping Authority (TSA)

System adds trusted timestamp:

```
Signature Time Certified by Independent Timestamp Service
```

Prevents backdating or manipulation.

---

# 6️⃣ DOCUMENT INTEGRITY CONTROL

After signing:

* Document locked
* Version frozen
* Editing disabled
* Any change invalidates signature

If amendment needed:

* New version created
* New signature cycle required

Full version history preserved.

---

# 7️⃣ NON-REPUDIATION MECHANISM

Each signature record includes:

* Verified identity
* Authentication method used
* IP address
* Device fingerprint
* Time of signing
* Hash of signed document

This ensures signer cannot deny action.

---

# 8️⃣ BID SUBMISSION PROTECTION

During bid submission (Logic 6):

* Bid encrypted at submission
* Signed by supplier
* Timestamped
* Locked until bid opening

Prevents:

* Post-deadline modifications
* Denial of submission
* Bid tampering

---

# 9️⃣ CONTRACT SIGNING FLOW

```
Contract Draft Generated
        ↓
Buyer Authorized Signatory Signs
        ↓
Supplier Authorized Signatory Signs
        ↓
System Verifies Certificates
        ↓
Document Locked
        ↓
Contract Activated
```

Both signatures required for enforceability.

